    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/45000126/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """The objective of this module is that students achieve a basic knowledge of the principles of nanoscience and nanotechnology, the properties of the main nanostructures, as well as the techniques used for their fabrication and characterisation. From the established microtechnology, the appearance and evolution of the main nanodevices will be reviewed, with a special focus on the fields of nanoelectronics, nanophotonics and nanobiotechnology. Finally, the module will include the application of such nanodevices in different areas relevant for structural and mainly functional material engineers, such as information and communication technologies, space, security, environment, domotics and nanomedicine.
From the content view, this module pursues opening the students mind to emerging ideas and technologies, and to provide a wide and multidisciplinary approach of the 21 c. science and technology, from the research towards the innovation. In the aptitude side, this module will increase their attitude and skill to think and relate contents; to research, ellaborate and present information, and to work in a team.
."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/fernando.calle%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/fernando.calle%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/j.pedros%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Nanotechnology"@es .

