<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/45000126/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The evaluation process will follow these guidelines:

CONTINUOUS EVALUATION: FINAL MARKS = 80 % exams + 20 % team work and presentation
Two partial exams will be done during the course and the end, around weeks 7 and 17. Each will count 40%. To pass, minimum grade in each exam should be >4/10.
The remaining 20% will be awarded from a team work and oral presentation given in the 12th to 14th weeks. This presentation is a compulsory, non-recoverable activity, due to its teamwork character. The weight will take into account the presentation itself (15%) and the participation during the workshop (5%).
Some recognition could also be given to those students who pass these exams from their individual contributions during classes, Moodle forums, etc.

GLOBAL EVALUATION
A global exam with two parts, each valued 40%, will be performed at the end of the module.
The remaining 20% will be awarded from the team work and oral presentation given in the 12th to 14th weeks.

EXTRAORDINARY CALL
An exam valued 80%
The remaining 20% will be awarded from the team work and oral presentation given in the 12th to 14th weeks.

In all cases, a complementary evaluation might take place to guarantee that original work has been performed."""@es ;
